    <title>Facebook - Badges - Customizing Privacy for post stops posting funnel in the middle</title>
    <description>
        <paragraph id="2">
            <sentence id="2.1">when the user wants to change the privacy option of a specific message they are able to use the little "lock" button to do that.</sentence>
            <sentence id="2.2">they should be able to return to the "post on wall" page once the save the settings and continue the posting funnel.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="4">
            <sentence id="4.1">Steps to Reproduce:</sentence>
            <sentence id="4.2">1 Go to badges page and click on a badge -&gt; the "Post to Wall" window appears.</sentence>
            <sentence id="4.3">2 click on the little "lock" icon on the bottom left corner -&gt; chose "Custom" on the little window that appears.</sentence>
            <sentence id="4.4">3 on the "Custom Privacy" window choose any option you like and click "save settings".</sentence>
            <sentence id="4.5">Actual Results:</sentence>
            <sentence id="4.6">The "Custom Privacy" window disappears and that is it.</sentence>
            <sentence id="4.7">No post to wall.</sentence>
            <sentence id="4.8">See attached video capture.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="5">
            <sentence id="5.1">Expected Results:  
The "Custom Privacy" window will disappear and the "Post to Wall" window returns.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
    </description>
